TITLE: Creating and Starting a GraphQL Yoga Server with Node.js
DESCRIPTION: Complete example demonstrating how to create a GraphQL schema, initialize a GraphQL Yoga server, and start a Node.js HTTP server. Includes schema definition with typeDefs and resolvers, and server configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphql-hive/graphql-yoga/blob/main/README.md#2025-04-15_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createServer } from 'node:http'
import { createSchema, createYoga } from 'graphql-yoga'

const yoga = createYoga({
  schema: createSchema({
    typeDefs: /* GraphQL */ `
      type Query {
        hello: String
      }
    `,
    resolvers: {
      Query: {
        hello: () => 'Hello from Yoga!'
      }
    }
  })
})

const server = createServer(yoga)

server.listen(4000, () => {
  console.info('Server is running on http://localhost:4000/graphql')
})
```

