TITLE: Custom Error Handling with GraphQLError
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to throw custom GraphQLErrors for expected error cases, such as resource not found scenarios. Includes user lookup implementation with custom error messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/graphql-hive/graphql-yoga/blob/main/website/src/content/docs/features/error-masking.mdx#2025-04-15_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { GraphQLError } from 'graphql'
import { createSchema, createYoga } from 'graphql-yoga'

const users = [
  { id: '1', login: 'Laurin' },
  { id: '2', login: 'Saihaj' },
  { id: '3', login: 'Dotan' }
]

const yoga = createYoga({
  schema: createSchema({
    typeDefs: /* GraphQL */ `
      type User {
        id: ID!
        login: String!
      }
      type Query {
        user(byId: ID!): User!
      }
    `,
    resolvers: {
      Query: {
        user: async (_, args) => {
          const user = users.find(user => user.id === args.byId)
          if (!user) {
            throw new GraphQLError(`User with id '${args.byId}' not found.`)
          }
          return user
        }
      }
    }
  })
})
```

